2001-05-22  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* configure.in:
	* Makefile.am:
	Move EXTRA_THEMES from the make file to the configure file.
	Small fix and fvwm-themes-extra-VERSION.tar main directory
	is now fvwm-themes-base-VERSION and not fvwm-themes-VERSION

	* Makefile.am:
	* rpm/Makefile.am:
	* rpm/fvwm-themes-*.spec.in:
	* configure.in:
	make rpm-{base,extra,themes}-this create the rpm package that
	correspond to the new tarballs build by the previous commits.
	make rpm-dist3 build all the gz tarballs and all the rpm but
	the full rpm (make rpm-dist or rpm-this for that).
	Warning: English checking and Russian translation needed in
	in the spec files

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	Added support for extra version "_x.x" for --create-pack with
	a --pack-extra-version option. New option --pack-prefix.

2001-05-22  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* Makefile.am:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	small improvements and fixes of the previous commit,
	s/--create-themes/--create-pack/

2001-05-21  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* Makefile.am:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	make dist3 build:
	- fvwm-themes-main-version.tar.gz with the base distribution plus
	  8 themes:
	  afterstep, cde, default, migo, multichoice, olicha, redmond98
	- fvwm-themes-extra-version.tar.gz with the extra themes:
	  awol, blackbox, brushmetal, nanogui, osx, spruce
	- ft-name-version.tar.gz for each extra themes name
	make dist4 build the corresponding bz2 tarballs and make dist{,2}
	are not changed.
	The fvwm-themes-extra and the ft-name-version tarballs can be installed
	with fvwm-themes-config [--site] --install tarballs

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	New option --create-themes name theme1 theme2 ... which create a tarball
	in the good formate made of theme1 theme2 ... from the site or user
	dir. New utils options --force-install and --tmp-dir.
 
	* themes/default/themes/settings/stroke/enabled
	Use A modifier in the place of N for the R context

