2001-03-31  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* themes/default/settings/iconstyles/{wm-icons,native}:
	use $.; now I remember why I didn't use it here and in */modules/main,
	this is to enable user versions of sub-files in ~/.fvwm to be Read,
	probably it is not a good idea to enable user versions of sub-files

	* bin/fvwm-themes-start.in:
	actually prepend bindir to PATH even if it is here, but not first;
	the problem is that PATH is now not that user had initially,
	but running wrong versions of fvwm and fvwm-themes utilities
	(if there are several instalations) is probably worse for us

	* devel/doc/style-guide.txt:
	moved this file from fvwm-themes-web as a part of its reorgonization;
	this style guide is successfully used in our company for many years :)

