2001-01-05  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	* themes/*/*.cfg:
	Implemented !reuse-dependencies, !reset-properties (4 forms) cfg
	directives in components affecting definitions of components, which
	are specified more than once - either reset or reuse the existing
	definitions, this enables not to specify any dependancies in *.cfg,
	if they are not different from the default ones. Not fully tested.
	The current defaults are probably good, but this may be changed.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	Small changes to the previous commit.
	I didn't really try a minimal reload yet.

	* TODO: added 2 items

2001-01-04  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	* themes/default/bindings:
	* themes/*/buttons:
	* themes/default/settings/stroke/*
	* themes/default/themes.cfg
	* themes/default/settings.cfg
	Starting minimal reload implementation. For simplification put
	the RemoveBindings, RemoveButtonsBindings and RemoveAllButtons
	functions into start-stop functions.
	Note: 1 - The minimal reload is really maximal: see the remarks
	in the fvwm-themes-config.in function "getReloadDependency".
	We must do something ...
	2 - The stop function is not well implemented and so drop do
	not use "minimal reload" ((un)lock work pretty well).
	3 - You can switch between global and "minimal" theme switching
	with the theme management menu (global is still the default):
	reload and refresh -> Use minimal/global switching. But first
	you need to make install, refresh the current theme and restart.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	added a --rm-cfg-cache option. Now we can refresh the current theme
	and rebuild or not the config cache file in the theme management
	menu.

