	* scripts/FvwmScript-ThemesCenter: s/restor/restore/

2000-08-13  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* scripts/FvwmScript-ThemesCenter:
	* scripts/FvwmScript-ThemeOptions:
	* scripts/Makefile.am:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	* NEWS:
	* TODO:
	A new FvwmScript for themes selection (and more in the future).
	This script use the same logic as FvwmScript-Menus: I've added
	a communication loop in fvwm-themes-config and the ThemesCenter
	(and ThemeOptions) communicate with fvwm-themes-config via
 	fvwm-themes-com. The ThemeCenter Theme Selector support normal
	component, component with choice, component with options and
	component with one level of sub component (with choices, but
	not with options). So, all the current themes are supported
	but the "settings" component (a special ThemeCenter config tool
	will be added one days for this special component). 
	Things to do for the themes selector: implement "drop" and
	finish "restore" (for opt/cho/sub). My problem with drop is:
	can we know before dropping if the dropping is not forbidden?
	The changes in fvwm-themes-config have almost an empty intersection
 	with the "old" code. Mikhael, feel free to do all the changes
	you want. The intersection is a modification in themes-rc-2:
	a menu entries for the ThemesCenter in the Theme Management
	menu.
	
