2000-06-29  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	- Fixed loading *-extra and other components, which are not yet in
	the current theme.
	- Add Drop/Info menu items to all components even complex ones.
	- Replaced memory implementation (removed 8 functions, added 2),
	memory is stored in _core component.
	- Now HASH in HASH in .cfg is supported too (represented by ':').
	- I had no time to learn why 'used' is needed and to get rid of it.

	* themes/migo/modules/*:
	Added options as an alternative way to how choices are handled
	in olicha/default themes.
	Changed Pager sizes, unfortunately there is a problem in FvwmPager.

	* themes/migo/background:
	* themes/migo/images/background/cyan-tile.pmg:
	New image, still not exactly what I want. :)

	* themes/default/bindings:
	* themes/*/buttons:
	Restored motif behavior of WindowsOps menu, it is possible to
	change it in personal bindings-extra or functions-extra.
	Renamed FuncFvwmActionOrWindowsOps2 to FuncFvwmActionOrWindowsOps,
	maybe someone wants to popup WindowsOps here immediately.

	* themes/*/colors[/*]:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	Finally moved 'ModuleSynchronous FvwmTheme' to core.

	* themes/*/sound:
	* themes/default/settings/sound-player/*:
	* themes/*/modules/main:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	FvwmEvent for sounds now started/stoped as 'FvwmEvent FvwmSoundEvent',
	this enables us to run other event modules.
	FuncFvwmStopModuleByAlias now requires 2 parameters (was 1).
	FuncFvwmRestartModuleByAlias now accepts an optional 3-rd parameter.

	* themes/default/menus-user:
	Moved some apps from my personal menus (I don't have all of them). 
	Games will be added later. There should be added support for
	ViewFile & EditFile, just like ViewFileTail.

2000-06-28  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	- Added support for (non permanent) sub component ("contains" cfg
 	command). 
	- Added a "memory stuff" for options and choices, this
	use a memory.cfg file in the user current theme directory.
	- Now only the only *.cfg file that are "automatically" load
	in the default file are theme.cfg and setting.cfg (this allows
	the default theme to get its own sub component, for modules
	for examples).
	Note: The new code is marked by a "# olicha" so that it is easy for 
	you Mikhael to see the diff. Of course most of these marks have to
	be removed in the future.
	The new "memory" code can be merged with the 'cc' code at a lot of 
	places, but I've prefered to use a more prudent method for lisibility
	and leave this for the future.

	* themes/{olicha,default}/modules.cfg:
	* themes/{olicha,default}/modules/*:
	Implemented "theme modules settings" for olicha and default.
	Will continue with the other themes if every body are happy
	with this.

	* configure.in:
	* Makefile.am:
	* forms/Makefile.am:
	* forms/FormThemeSettings.
	* themes/default/menus
	Create an autoconfed forms directory and add the FormThemeSettings.
 	of Alex (with some changes).

	* bin/fvwm-themes-menuapp.in:
	Fixed the --site option

	* scripts/ScriptFvwmMenu:
	Fixed the position of the text in the Lists, thanks to the new
	Get{Min,Max}Value instructions.

	* themes/default/settings.cfg:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in
	stroke requires bindings. Added a new cfg command "external-imagepath".
	See the detail in fvwm-themes-config.in (the stuff does not work).
	Mikhael do you want to finish it?
	
2000-06-16  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config.in:
	Applied a one line patch from migo
	
	* themes/*/modules/main:Fvwm{IconMan,IconBox,TaskBar,WinList}:
	Enabled animation: fvwm is not more confused with "double" animation
	
	* themes/*/button:
	* themes/default/bindings:
	Completed the 2<->3 mouse switching
	New function FuncFvwmActionOrWindowsOps2: first arg for one click
	WindowsOps2 for double click.
	Use the above functions when needed, but use Delete in the place of
	FuncFvwmDelete since if I use it I've got a:
	 [FVWM][ExecuteFunction]: <<ERROR>> No such command 'FuncFvwmDelete'
	I'm quite confused with variable expansion ...
	
	* themes/default/functions:
	"Fix" FuncFvwmIconifySameResource: replace C by I
	
	* themes/default/bindings*:
	* themes:default/settings/stroke/enable:
	Switch Mouse 2<->3 is almost ok for stroke: the pb is that
	FuncFvwmMoveOrRaiseLower does not work with stroke replace it
	by RasieLower in this case (stroke + 2<->3=yes)
	
	* bin/fvwm-tehemes-menuapp.in
	* scripts/ScriptFvwmMenus
	Some bug fixes.

