2000-06-09  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* scripts/ScriptFvwmMenus:
	A menus editor for fvwm-themes! Use fvwm-themes-menuapp via 
	fvwm-themes-com. It is alpha!

	* Scripts/ScriptFvwmIconBrowser
	* scripts/scriptFvwmBrowser
	Some browser scripts (use fvwm-themes-script)

	* bin/fvwm-themes-menuapp.in:
	The fvwm-themes menus (and more in the future) utilities. Runed at
	installation for parsing the menus and remove the applications not
	in the machine.
	
	* bin/fvwm-themes-com.in:
	The fvwm-themes communicator: allows communication between a FvwmScript
	script (or any other "programs") and a program that run in the 
	"background"

	* bin/fvwm-themes-script.in:
	A library for FvwmScript script
	
	* configure.in:
	* Makefile.am:
	* scripts/Makefile.am:
	* bin/Makefile.am
	Autoconfiscation of the scripts dir and add the new scripts
	update the bin Makefile.am and check for mknod in configure.in

	* themes/default/styles:
	Some styles for  the new FvwmScript scripts
	
	* themes/default/desktop: resatblish MouseFocusClickRaisesOn :)
	
	* themes/default/startup: remove old read "options". Now this
	file is empty!
	
	* themes/{default,awol}/sound:
	* themes/{theme with a xpm/png background}/background
	Replace FVWM_USERHOME by FT_DATADIR, comment the read command in awol
	sound. Do I do a stupid thing?

	* themes/default/themes.cfg: modules requires styles.

	* themes/default/menus-*:
	For technical reason for the GUI ScriptFvwmMenus, remove the
	{Add,Destroy}Menu MenuFvwm{Programs,Personal}. Reaname 
	menus-programs by menus-user and move in it MenuFvwmShell,
	MenuFvwmSystem, MenuFvwmScreenSaver. New menu MenuFvwmWindowManger
	and some work in the programs and systems menus.

2000-06-02  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Current complex components or the ones with options/choices are
	now listed first.
	Implemented support for any complex data in --show-value, try, f.e.
	[f-t-c] --component settings/gnome/user-menu --show-value choice.
	Added --show-dir parameter.
	--fresh parameter (i.e. Refresh the current theme) now preserves
	current options and choices.
	
2000-05-27  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-start.in:
	Fixed options (set and show). Options are now available in
	component using FuncFvwmReadOption-component:option.
	Added --component, --show-value parameters.
	Exit with an error if no parameters given.

	* themes/default/settings.cfg:
	* themes/default/settings/sound-player:
	Renamed settings/sound component to settings/sound-player.

