	(reported by Jason).

2000-04-05  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	* images/*/*:
	Moved bb-*, osx-* and migo-* images back to the local places.
	Now colors component requires local images/decor and images/menuback.

	* themes/migo/colors: added sh and hi colors to active menu colorset

	* themes/default/menus: added the void definition of MenuFvwmPersonal
	back (it is ok, menus-my or similar should require menus).

	* themes/default/menus-programs:
	removed duplications in MenuFvwmInternet

	* themes/migo/modules/main:
	Replaced not working -x wm-icons-config test with another one.

	* themes/default/menus:
	Added MenuFvwmWindowRefresh, MenuFvwmWindowUtility submenus
	with additional (hopefully useful) window operations.

	* themes/default/startup: component renamed, was "start".

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	* scripts/ScriptNoteMessage:
	* themes/default/styles:
	Script renamed from ScriptUtilsMessage and moved hardcoded title.

	* themes/default/styles:
	Temporarily added DefaultColorset, until a permanent place.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Moved windowlook to read-first components, because Style * BorderWidth
	should be before other BorderWidth styles (in styles* components).

	* options/stroke/enabled:
	added one additional binding for each calculator and www; rewordings.

	* options/iconstyles/iconstyles: slightly updated

	* themes/migo/cursors: added STROKE cursor (plus is not good IMHO)

	* themes/default/menus:
	* themes/default/bindings:
	Small changes in WindowOps2 menu (hopefully imporovements):
	replaced Delete & Destroy with Close, Restore item now restores
	maximizing and shading, not only iconifying.
	Replaced FuncFvwmMaximize or FuncFvwmIconify with Maximize and
	Iconify in WindowOps2, we should have the real operations here.
	Fixed cut&paste errors in MenuFvwmWindowStyle.

	* themes/default/menus:
	* themes/redmond98/modules/main:startmenu:
	Added links to fvwm and fvwm-themes home pages.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	banner options is now on by default,
	s/FuncFvwmOptionsUse/FuncFvwmThemesUseOption/

	* themes/*/colors:
	massive clean up (more is needed), added the colorset for FvwmScroll
	and 5 colorsets for different terminal types.

	* scripts/ScriptNoteMessage: use colorset 0 (feedback window)
	* themes/default/{functions,functions-appbind,menus,bindings}:
	Use own colorsets for special function windows, xterms, root xterms
	and FvwmConsole; ShowMessage uses FvwmForm's colorset.

	* themes/osx/modules/main:FvwmMenuBarButtons:
	Fixed position of one submenu, small renaming.

	* Makefile:
	On installation, if found, personal themes is copied from the
	existing (old) themes/ and --use'd. This may cause compatibility
	problems when personal theme is not up to date...

	* themes/blackbox/images/menuback/face.xpm:
	Reduced number of colors and fixed one buggy black line.
	We should support guys with 8bpp. blackbox/images/decor/* should be
	reduced/improved too...

	* themes/*/windowlook:
	All files are minimized and now have the same format.
	I have removed headers, because I don't think that theme name should
	be inside fixed-format "look" components. Of course, I may be wrong.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	* themes/blackbox/images/modulecolor/*:
	Moved images used in colors component from module/ to modcolor/.

	* themes/awol/*:
	Added new awol theme from Alex after massive editing.
	Crazy colors and sounds. :-)

2000-03-19  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	* options/session/{regular,gnome}:
	* themes/afterstep/modules/main:FvwmIconMan:
	* doc/FAQ:
	Fix (I hope) the "session hang". Weakned the Session support now
 	GNOME is not auto detected: you need to choose your session support
	as an option (gnome is the default). The definition of
	FuncFvwmFvwmOrSessionOrGnome is in the new files 
	options/session/{regular,gnome} and use perl in the place of
	the shell.

	* themes/blackbox/buttons,colors,images/
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Try to fix blackbox "colors". New global function (in themes-rc) 
	FuncFvwmIfModules mod action1 action2
	where mod is the name of a modules theme, action1 is executed if
	the curre nt modules is mod and action2 is executed if not.
	This function used in colors to load either the pixmap 
	module/TheToolbar700.xpm or a gradient for colorset 10.

	* themes/default/menus: Fix the root xterm

	* themes/default/style: added a style for ScriptUtilsMessage and
	gnome icons.

	* themes/osx/colors: Fix colors 10 to 13 (use inactive title)

	* themes/osx/desktop: Fix GlobalOptions !

	* themes/olicha/modules/main:FvwmXappletButtons:
	* themes/redmond98/modules/main:FvwmBarButtons:
	Fix some colors of xlock and xload
	
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Fix the panel stays put gnome option. The default Layers need to
	be read before any layer command.

	* script/{ScriptUtilsMessage,README}:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	A new script for displaying a message during theme switch.
	
