	Use the inactive menu color as the main color

	* themes/olicha/desktop: allows some horizontal scrolling

	* themes/osx/modules/main:FvwmOsxButtons:
	* themes/blackbox/main:FvwmXXButtons:
	* options/autoraise/modules:
	The Previous functions work in the "same way" with the MouseFocus
	or NeverFocus or ClickToFocus style, so there are no more problems
	with autoraise/modules option.
	
2000-03-07  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* themes/default/functions-appbind:
	* themes/default/functions:
	* themes/default/main:FvwmTaskBar:
	* themes/afterstep/main:FvwmAsButtons:
	* themes/olicha/main:FvwmStartAppsButtons:
	* themes/olicha/main:FvwmXappletsButtons:
	* themes/olicha/main:FvwmTaskBar:
	* themes/osx/main:FvwmOsxAppsButtons:
	* themes/redmond98/main:FvwmBarButtons:
	* themes/redmond98/main:startmenu:
	* themes/redmond98/main:FvwmTaskBar:
	* themes/wm-icons/main:FvwmCompactButtons:
	* doc/FAQ:
	New files themes/default/functions-appbind. This file contains
	functions for starting applications. These functions are used
	in FvwmButtons buttons so that editing this file change the
	applications started by these buttons in all themes :)
	These functions are also used in menu and in a well configurated
 	FvwmTaskBar (for the mail) and some functions from
	themes/default/functions have been moved in this file.
	The defaults are not very intelligent! Any comments and changes
	are welcome. Any way this file has been done for edition!

	* themes/redmond98/main:FvwmDesker: fixed size of the desker vs
	the size of the buttons that popup the Desker

	* themes/osx/images/buttons/*: try to fix the buttons on a dark
	background

	* themes/osx/colors: fixed active menu colorset

	* themes/*/windowlook: renamed "decorations" by "windowlook"

	* options/stroke/{disabled,enabled}:
	* doc/FAQ:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Added support for stroke. options/current/stroke is read by
 	themes/default/bindings.

	* options/iconstyles/iconstyles:
	* options/iconstyles/wm-icons:
	* options/iconstyles/wm-icons:imagepath:
	* options/iconstyles/native:
	* themes/default/styles:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	All the icons styles is now in one file options/iconstyles/iconstyles.
	native just ask to read this file and wm-icons read this file plus
	wm-icons:menu. Moreover, options/current/iconstyles is read in
	themes/*/styles. Of course, minor change in fvwm-themes-config was 
	needed. Note that options/iconstyles/wm-icons:imagepath is "read
	first" when needed and fvwm-themes-config control that.

	* themes/default/menus:
	* themes/default/menus-programs:
	* themes/redmond98/modules/main:startmenu:
	* images/winXX-startmenu/personal.xpm:
	Move MenuFvwmPrograms in themes/default/menus-programs and add to
	many entries, but my idea here is to do a very very big menu 
	(witout gnome and kde apps) and to do a perl script that parse it
 	to retain only the installed applications.
	Add a MenuFvwmPersonal menu.

	* themes/wm-icons/*
	* themes/migo/modules/*
	Move wm-icons into migo
	
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	* options/gnome/panel-staysput/{enable,disabled}:
	Added an option that try to force the panel to be StaysPut.
	This does not work perfectly, currently I need to slide/unslide
	the panel before the option work. Also, the option is not 
	really "dynamic" (even after a restart).
	Note: Currently I've a problem with the panel it start only
	20sec after fvwm finish its startup!
	
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	* themes/*/modules/main:
	* themes/afterstep/main:FvwmIconman:
	* themes/default/bindings:
	* themes/default/menu:
	* themes/default/style:
	* options/autoraise/modules:
	Added Session/Gnome support. In themes-rc there is a new function
	FuncFvwmFvwmOrSessionOrGnome, this function take 3 arguments, the 
	first argument is executed if fvwm is started "alone", the second 
	argument is executed if fvwm is started via a session manager but 
	gnome and the 3rd one is executed if fvwm is started via a gnome 
	session. See FuncFvwmThemesConfigAndUpdate (for theme switching),
	themes/default/menu: (for exiting), themes/default/bindings (for
	gnome button) and themes/afterstep/main:FvwmIconman, for some
	example of use of this function.
	Moreover, themes (switching) is NoSession/Session award for the 
	modules themes (not NoSession/Session/Gnome award, but we can do 
	that if we think we need that). The fvwm session init function
	are used, of course, and there is a FuncFvwmSessionStartThemeModules
	function. In general, under session less modules are started and
	in fact I've done that so that a default panel does not overlap with
	some fvwm modules ...
	Notes: - in menu "Yes, Really Quit" and "Yes, Quit & Save Session" do
	not work under xsm. We may define a FuncFvwmFvwmOrSessionOrGnomeOrXsm
	if one ask for a true xsm support. However, I've added a style line
	for xsm.
 	- We may try to be more session/gnome award, e.g., redefines
	FormFvwmQuitVerify and do some options session award (e.g.,
	background: disabled, disabled for session, theme ...)
	- Todo: add the option for gnome: dynamic desk (default) /
 	4 desks (GnomeShowDesks 4).
	
2000-02-27  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* themes/*/colors:
	* themes/*/decorations:
	* themes/*/menustyles:
	* themes/*/modules/*:
	* themes/default/functions
	* themes/default/menus
	* images/{decor,menuback}:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	First minimal implementation of "colors".
	colors defines all the colors for a theme and use FvwmTheme.
	It must be readed before decorations, menustyles, buttons,
	menu and modules/main (and any file that may use a colorset).
	Read a colors file for details !
	fvwm-themes-config change: replaced decorations by colors at line 576,
	added FuncFvwmStopFvwmThem in FuncFvwmThemesConfigAndUpdate.
	I'm really sorry but I put back to the global images directory
	the decor (osx, migo, blackbox) and the menuback (osx, blackbox).
	I do that because I cannot modify fvwm-themes-config so that
	fvwm-themes-config computes the good image path.
        I've changed the colors of aftersetp: the colors are taken from
	afterstep 1.8.
	Of course there are some bugs in the implementation. Some came
	from fvwm itself (there are bugs in FvwmPager and FvwmButtons
	Colorset implementation). These lead me some times to do bad
	coding (e.g., osx/modules/main:FvwmOsxButtons) or to do things
	that I do not like for colors (e.g., afterstep/modules/main:
	FvwmAsButtons).
	
	* themes/blackbox: Try to do so that blackbox is more compatible 
	with the other themes. Still need a lot of work !

	* themes/afterstep/modules/*: Added an afterstep modules theme 
	("from" afterstep 1.8)
	
	* themes/afterstep/background: Added a background

	* themes/afterstep/buttons: Fixed the "menu button" bindings

	* images/button: Replaced the as-window-iconify.xpm by the one 
	in afterstep 1.8.

	* themes/osx/modules/*: Added a modules theme (need FvwmM4)

	* themes/osx/background: Added a background

	* themes/osx/desktop: Emulate mwm (better for the modules theme)

	* scripts/*: small fixes

	* README, NEWS: updated
	
2000-02-15  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	Preparing the first public alpha release.
	All initial documentation and README's updated.

	* themes/default/functions:
	minor changes to FuncFvwm{Iconify,Maximize[VH]*}.
	Moved FuncFvwmIconifySameResource from default/bindings.
	FuncFvwmShowMessage has title parameter, new FuncFvwmShowButtonInfo.
	New configurable FuncFvwmRunInXterm.

	* themes/*/buttons:
	Renamed FuncFvwm s/ShowMessage/ShowButtonInfo/,
	now EOLN is ^n, TAB is ^t in the messages to avoid quoting problems.

	* themes/*/*:
	Renamed FuncFvwm s/ManPager/ViewManPage/, s/FileViewer/ViewFile/,
	s/FileEditor/EditFile/, s/WebBrowser/OpenURL/.

	* themes/default/menus: added MenuFvwmSystem.

	* themes/*/modules/main:{FvwmTaskBar,FvwmIconMan}:
	fixed/added 'Popup MenuFvwmWindowOps2 Mouse c -102m' as Mouse3 action.
	* themes/*/modules/main:FvwmWinList:
	fixed/added 'Popup MenuFvwmWindowOps2 Mouse -105m c' as Mouse3 action.

	* fvwm-themes-config:
	minor changes (like '*' instead of '+' for the current option);
	init functions are now destroyed on theme switch to save memory.

	* options/iconstyles/*: minor updates from wm-icons package.

	* images/16x16-general/ball-*.xpm: removed unused icons.

	* themes/default/bindings:
	Added experimental support for folks without mouse button 2 -
	simulate some Mouse2 bindings on decorations/window by Ctrl-Mouse1.

	* scripts/*:
	* themes/olicha/modules/*:
	* themes/blackbox/modules/main:FvwmXXButtons:
	* options/autoraise/modules:
	* themes/redmond98/modules/main:FvwmDesker:
	* themes/olicha/menustyle:
	Olivier's patch, new applets and minor fixes.

	* themes/default/modules/main:
	Fixed "Normal icons" menu entry.

2000-02-10  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* themes/default/menus:
	moved configuration menus up, X config forms are now in FVWM config.
	fvwm-menu-xlock option --icon replaced with --icon-item.

	* themes/redmond98/background:
	changed ms flame to flying fvwm, why should we mention ms at all?..

	* images/{16x16,48x48}-general: updated from the latest developement
	version of wm-icons.

	* images/:
	Created new alias bar to enable wm-icons theme without wm-icons
	package being installed; removed decor/; renamed module/ to 32x32/.
	updated 32x32/image-viewer.xpm icon.
	* images/16x16-general:
	Renamed ball-*.xpm; new kde.xpm; gnome.xpm 86 colors reduced to 20.

	* Renamed image alias module/mini to 16x16 everywhere.
	This is half-fixed way, i.e. there is a possibility to change to
	other 16x16 icon set, like 16x16-kde, for real fixed way -
	use the real icon set names, i.e. 16x16-general/xterm.xpm.
	* themes/olicha/modules/main:FvwmStartAppsButtons
	Similarly changed mini/ to 16x16/, since the geometry is fixed.

	* Moved images for migo and osx themes to the local places, it is
	unbeliviable that these images could be reused anyway.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Now image dirs are not listed in component list, image dir links
	are updated automatically when needed (some hardcoding for now).
	New rc files are now named themes-rc and themes-rc-2.

	* themes/olicha/modules/main:FvwmStartWinOpsButtons: replaced
	close action with delete, because there is destroy, is it ok?

	* themes/redmond98/modules/:
	main:FvwmTaskBar: fixed the menu position;
	Problem: all pagers are not proportional; set DeskTopSize to 3x2?

	* themes/*/theme.xml: removed currently before the real solution.

	* themes/wm-icons/modules/main:FvwmMyPagerButtons:
	Added a new module. Problem: FvwmPager should accept -g!
	Now used again absolute geometry for pager, since there is FvwmDesker.

	* themes/default/bindings:
	Shift-Ctrl-Mouse2 now calls FvwmDesker, not FvwmPager,
	Shift-Alt-Tab now is supplement (skip) version of Alt-Tab,
	removed Escape bindings, minor changes to icon bindings.

	* themes/*/buttons:
	some standardization changes, swapped MenuFvwmWindowMove and
	MenuFvwmWindowGroupOps bindings (I hope it's ok), deleted modifiers,
	tried to use only customizable functions and not real commands.
	Imlemented inline button help using Ctrl-Alt + click on button.

	* themes/default/functions:
	New functions: FuncFvwmShowMessage, FuncFvwmIconify, FuncFvwmDelete,
	FuncFvwmMaximizeVertically, FuncFvwmMaximizeHorizontally.

	* images/*/penguin.xpm, themes/*/modules/main:FvwmTaskBar:
	Replaced to be 16x16 and moved from winXX-startmenu/ to 16x16/ dir.

	* doc/FAQ, doc/README.1st, AUTHORS, COPYING:
	Created some initial documentation and standard files.

2000-02-03  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* themes/olicha/modules/*: Added olicha modules themes. Need some
	works ...
	* themes/olicha/README: Added help instructions.
	* themes/*/desktop: Replaced GlobalOpts by the new stryles. Hope
	that dominik will not change ClickToFocusClickRaises.
