	so that we can use "fixed icons" in modules (i.e., not dependent on
	wm-icons).
	* themes/redmond98/modules/main:FvwmBarButtons:
	Use "fixed icons" for the win ops container
	* themes/redmond98/modules/main: Fixed a missprint
	* themes/default/functions: Removed FuncFvwmRemoveAllButtons since
	it is in rc.
	* themes/default/menus: Again modules ...
	* options/sound/*: added an entries in Regular modules menus (if
	the option is not disabled)
	* options/autoraise/modules: added an entries in Regular modules menu
	(if the option is enabled), and remove one in Theme modules menu.

	* makefile
	* scripts/: 
	New directories (global :) for scripts
	* scripts/ScriptAppletDay: an AS & WM compatible applet for the
	day (need date). Work in progress !
	* script/ScriptAppletMixer: an AS & WM compatible applet to control
	sound (need aumix). Work in progress !
	Currently, the background is blue, maybe we can reserve a colorset
	for the applets background ?

2000-02-03  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* themes/*/modules/*: 
	* themes/default/menus:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config (hard coded part):
	Some of the modules are restarted and not only started, add
	functions FuncFvwmRestartModule and FuncFvwmRestartModuleByAlias
	in rc (there are always used so ...). Also move FuncFvwmRemoveButtons.
	Do some modifications about modules menus ... Do not know if this
	ok.

	* themes/default/bindings:
 	* themes/*/buttons:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config (hard coded part):
	New function FuncFvwm{RemoveBindings,ButtonsBindings} that remove 
	the bindings.
	These functions are used by FuncFvwmThemesConfigAndUpdate

	* themes/*/modules/*:
	Use FvwmDesker alias for the 4 desks pagers. 
	Since desktop is now in modules the MenuFvwmMoveWindow is with
	DesktopSize (i.e.: with the pager config) and with the Desker
	config if there are a move between desk menu entries.

	* themes/modules/balackbox/*: Some fixes. Do not now if there
	are ok. Details: 
	- Added Style * NoIcon, 
	- Remove Style * MiniIcon aicon and put false for iconman miniicon
	(the result is not very different and this is need for that the stuff 
	works with other themes).
	- A Config for a desker. Need to add Toolbar100.xpm
	
	* themes/default/menus: Add MenuFvwmEditors in MenuFvwmPrograms

	* options/*:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config (hard coded part):
	Now current contains symlink with fixed name which is the
	name of the "working" directories. The options are ready to
	be started independently via some functions: 
	FuncFvwm{Stop,Start}Option{Animate,Sound, ...}

	* images/16x16-general: added kde.xpm and gnome.xpm. 
	Of course this cause a problem with wm-icons.

	* themes/*/buttons:
	* themes/*/decorations:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config (getThemeComponentList,sortThemeComponent):
	Try to do so that buttons and decorations of different themes work
	together. Main idea: put the definitions of the colors of the 
	buttons in decorations and put the TitleStyle Height in buttons.
	Moreover, decorations are now readed before buttons: this leads
	to 3 new lines in fvwm-themes-config.
	I've gotten Some difficulty to really destroy the previous buttons 
	definitions. Also, I and we will need to edit some buttons and
	decor.

2000-01-25  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* themes/blackbox: added new theme from Jos

	* themes/default/menus: several additions and "improvements"

	* themes/*/{desktop,modules/main}: moved DeskTopSize from desktop
	to modules (FvwmPager)

	* themes/wm-icons/modules/main:FvwmPager: specifying the size for the
	pager is not very good, FvwmPagerDeskTopScale is better, this is
	needed for Ctrl-Mouse2 and Ctrl-Shift-Mouse2 to work propertly;
	but now probably the pager is too small on small monitors...

	* everywhere (many places):
	s/FuncFvwmSt{op,art}ModulesTheme/FuncFvwmSt{op,art}ThemeModules/
	s/FuncFvwmSt{op,art}BackgroundTheme/FuncFvwmSt{op,art}ThemeBackground/
	s/MenuFvwmModulesTheme/MenuFvwmStartThemeModules/,
	s/MenuFvwmStopModule/MenuFvwmStopRegularModules/,
	added menus MenuFvwmStartRegularModules and MenuFvwmStopThemeModules.
	Regular modules are all normal modules, which should run out of box.
	The modules menu is rearanged (more structured now).

	* themes/default/modules/main: moved modules config to separate files;
	removed session initialization functions, it may be confusing not to
	get anything in gnome and it is ok to use both panel and modules,
	just not with every theme (wm-icons modules work well with panel).

	* themes/*/modules/main:
	Tried to keep the files in the same order.

	* images/: winXX startmenu icons moved to winXX-startmenu/

	* themes/default/functions:
	added FuncFvwmWebBrowser to view web documents
	* themes/redmond98/modules:startmenu:
	used FuncFvwmWebBrowser and added some menu icons

2000-01-25  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* NEWS, TODO: new files added

	* Renamed audiofiles/ to sounds/ everywhere.
	* options/iconstyles/standard: renamed to ./native.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	--expand option is added for external use;
	some clean up in hard-coded parts, rewrite is needed;
	prefix "+" instead of postfix "(current)" for options, should I use
	this also for themes instead of "(used)"?

	* makefile: backup fvwm-themes-config during instalation. I was
	angry when all my changes (for 2 days) were lost today...

	* themes/default/menus:
	some rearrangements and optimizations in window option menus,
	most of the menus now have mini icon, I am not very happy about this,
	more work on icons is needed.

	* wm-icons: added pager configuration and small clean up;
	Renamed CompactButtons to FvwmCompactButtons.

	* images/: removed unneded .xvpics/ and .directory.

	* themes/*/*: small rearrangements in functions and menus.

2000-01-24  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>

	* themes/redmond98/modules/main:FvwmBarButtons:
	Resize a lit bit.

	* themes/olicha/desktop: was forgetted.

	* Move all the icons into images/ and update the following files
	so that things work: afterstep/buttons, migo/decorations,
	olicha/{background,buttons}, osx/{menustyle,decorations}
	redmond98/{background,buttons,modules/main:FvwmBarButtons,
	modules/main:FvwmTaskBar,modules/main:startmenu}

	* Added 48x48-general and a general directories which is a
 	superset of 16x16-general. Added symlink: norm --> 48x48 and
	menu,mini --> general. These stuff is allways in the imagepath,
	but it is wm-icons compatible (wm-icons can over-write the icons
	names).
	
	* fvwm-themes-config:
	Change $imagePath so that the above change works.

	* Now what follows is an experimental (big) stuff:
	Added a new top directory called options/ that gives support for:
	- Animation (started or not started)
	- Sound effect (started with esdplay, rplay, or rplayd or not started,
	it will be easy to use others sound players. This does not define the
	sounds effect, only defines if FvwmEvent start or not and also
 	defines the sound player).
	- Modules Auto raise.
	- Background: use the theme bacground or not. It can be session/
	nosession sensitive and take in account the backer in the future.
	- iconstyle: standard, wm-icons, or disabled (disabled not work). 
	- KDE: various kde menu (with styles support or not). KFM bugoptions.
	- Gnome: various gnome menu (gtk or fvwm).

	All these allow to suppress the following files/dir in themes/:
	default/start, default/iconstyle, fvwm-icons/, {disable}/, 
	olicha/modules/modules-auto-raise, wm-icons/iconstyle.
	 
	Also, it needs a very bad hack of fvwm-themes-config: I've
	indicate the news stuff by "# New nbr.lines/bloc". It is bad
	because: 1. Stuff is hard coded 2. Identation is not compatible
	(never succeed to do so that a good .emacs for perl work ...).
	But an important point is that the stuff work :) and to be not
	hard coded a kind of options.xml is needed ...

	* Added default/sound and .fvwm/audiofiles/ with 4 audiofiles and
	some symlinks (I'm happy with this sound, but add_window.au). I
	think that in the futur we can done theme "a la wm-icons":
	some sound directories and symlinks from the "action" to some
	sounds.

	* default/menus and redmond98/modules/main:startmenu:
	replace MenuFvwmUtilities by MenuFvwmPrograms and put "Utilities"
	one level down with MenuFvwmGraphics and MenuFvwmInternet.
	This change is needed by the KDE/Gnome menu stuff.
	
	* Added "BusyCursor DynamicMenu True" in ALL themes/menustyle.

	* Update the makefile: images, options, audiofiles are installed
	and "uninstalled" as themes.

	* README: suppress the note about fvwm-icons :)
	
2000-01-18  migo  <migo@homemail.com>

	* themes/*:
	Many small corrections in menus, functions, spacing and wording.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Now 2 files are created: rc and rc2. .fvwm2rc is obsolete again. :)
	'env FVWM_USERHOME=~/.fvwm fvwm2 -f rc' is needed to start fvwm.
	rc file contains some functions to use/reset themes and loads rc2.
	Added --generate-rc and --xmessage (internal) options.
	ModulePath is now set in rc2 file, like ImagePath.
	Added README for each theme, is this needed?

	* themes/*/background:
	Renamed [Func]FvwmQuitBackgroundTheme to FuncFvwmStopBackgroundTheme
	and image subdir background/ to rootback/ (?).
	-mod 2x2 background changed to solid (looks better for move/resize).

	* themes/*/menustyles:
	Renamed to menustyle, initially I thought to put there not only *
	but also WindowList etc., but this should be thought later.
	All menustyle files have the same format (everything, but colorsets).

	* themes/*/{decorations,desktop}:
	Tried to keep the files in the same order.

	* themes/redmond98/images/modules/*: renamed to largebar/,
	Shrinked all 34x34 images to 32x32; striped the signature of
	netscape.xpm; replaced kview.xpm (image.xpm) from kde2 (too much
	colors) with the one from kde1; replaced term.xpm, other changes.
	More work is probably needed.
	* themes/redmond98/images/button/*:
	* themes/redmond98/buttons:
	Renamed s/winXX./window-/ to be wm-icons compatible.
	* themes/redmond98/modules:
	Renamed *.main files to main:* - probably temporarily.
	* themes/redmond98/modules/*:
	* themes/redmond98/images/*:
	Renamed some image subdirs, removed module path prefix.

	* themes/olicha/modules/modulesauto:
	Renamed to auto-raise-modules (?).
	* themes/olicha/images/button/*:
	* themes/olicha/buttons:
	Renamed s/mac./window-/ to be wm-icons compatible.

	* themes/default/bindings: added transient pager to root, restored
	previous bindings to borders (mouse 1 & 2) until we get a consensus

	* themes/default/menu: restored some things about WindowStyle menu

	* themes/osx/*: added new theme

	* themes/wm-icons/modules/main: last minute change: the alias 'button'
	used by CompactButtons renamed to 'bar' (smallbar better?).
	I will rename with in the next version of wm-icons too.

	NOTE: I restored/changed several things (I was too busy), but this
	does not mean I am against these things, it just means that
	I suggest it differently. Feel free to re-restore again. :)

	TODO: I didn't change wm-icons theme, I will.

2000-01-15  olicha  <olivier.chapuis@free.fr>
 	
	* ChangeLog: Creating this file

	* README:
	* Makefile:
 	* New file system.fvwm2rc
	Temporary (?) change. I added a .fvwm2rc file for
	theme switching (needed for modules theme switching and also
	background switching).
	So fvwm-themes with this version need to be started by:
	          env FVWM_USERHOME=~/.fvwm fvwm2
	Any way, I think that a file that is read only at (re)start is
	a good thing: We surely need some functions that are always
	needed (e.g., FuncFvwmRemoveButtons, FuncFvwmRestartModule, ...).
	
	* themes/Redmond98/*: Add windoze98 theme, most part came from 
	system.fvwm2rc-sample-95 or will be in it. 

	* themes/olicha/*: My theme ...
	
	* themes/default/menus:
	New menus MenuFvwmScreenSaver, MenuFvwmFvwmConfiguration,
	MenuFvwmXConfiguration, MenuFvwmHelp (with a sub menu
	MenuFvwmFvwmManPage), MenuFvwmWindowMove, MenuFvwmWindowClassOps, 
	MenuFvwmWindowPickClassOps, MenuFvwmPickWindowStyle.
	Added StaysOnTop, StaysPut, StaysOnBottom to the MenuFvwmWindowStyle
	menu (need to add the Func: FuncFvwmStyleAndRecapture)
	Replace some window-shade.xpm by window.xpm (and add window.xpm
	into images/menu)
	
	Question: Do we need to split menus in rootmenus, winopsmenus,
 	utilitiesmenu ?
	Where we put the "user programs", in utilitiesmenu ?
	
	* themes/default/modules/main:
	* themes/redmond98/modules/*:
	* themes/olicha/modules/modulesauto:
	* themes/wm-icons/modules/main:
	* themes/default/menu:
	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Added modules support for so called "visible" modules: Buttons,
	IconMan, IconBox, Pager, TaskBar, WinList (and Icon and Auto).
 	Details:
	- Removed most of the "read config default" in fvwm-theme-config
        - A proposal for a modules spec:
	  + Configuration of the visible modules. This config is in main
	  (e.g., default/modules/main) or the config is in others files
	  and are read by main (e.g., redmond98/main). Moreover, a module
	  config must contains is style (if it wants to be different than
	  the style defined in desktop): Title/Notitle, 
	  TitleAtTop/TitleAtBottom (if title), Layers (OnTop, OnBottom, Put),
	  eventually NoHandles, if needed Border and Handles width,
	  WindowListSkip/Hit, CirculateSkip/Hit, Sticky/Slippery,
	  maybe others if a guys want to use a special style for a
	  module we need to restore the style when switching ...
	  + Icon Grid, SlipperyIcon/StickyIcon, IconTitle/NoIconTitle and
 	   icon style Icon/NoIcon in the start func (I think that I forget
	   one or two icon style ?).
	  + Modules to (re)start
	  + Function for switching between modules theme:
	    FuncFvwmStartModulesTheme and FuncFvwmQuitModulesTheme
	  + Creation of MenuFvwmModulesTheme linked to the MenuFvwmRoot
	    via MenuFvwmModules
	  + We can have "optional" components: a module definition and 
	    starting/switching/menu stuff (without destruction) in a file with 
	    a different name and witch is read after modules/main (we need to
	    have the possibility to disable such a component):
 	    modules/olicha/modulesauto (I cannot live without this) give an 
	    example.
	  + I think that all our modules name have to be of the form
	    Fvwm* and if the name is an alias for FvwmFoo of the form Fvwm*Foo

	- Done some work in wm-icons/modules:
	Compactbuttons to main and done some works so that it respects
	the spec. Added the pager so that CompactButtons is almost a
	modules theme alone. Move the "change icons menu" into 
	MenuFvwmFvwmConfi. 
 	
	TODO:  
	- A better wm-icons (done some works for wm-icons, almost ok, 
	  need to configure at least one of the following modules: IconMan, 
	  WinList, IconMan or TaskBar and do a better config for the pager 
	  (miniicon!)).
 	- I've work on modules/default, but it will be good that some one 
	  else work on this so it is more a default (any way I start with
	  fvwm default)
	and do a better config for the pager (miniicon!)).
	- A migo, olicha, and afterstep modules/main.
	- I think it will be better if in MenuFvwm(Theme)Modules some
	of the modules (Buttons, TaskBar, Pager ...) are restarted and
	not just started. Currently impossible because of the existence of
  	multi-pager with the same name ...
	
	PROBLEMS: A lot :)
	Pager: It is natural to use two pagers, one for the current desk the
	other one for 2 or 3 or 4 desk. Unfortunately, the Pager does not
	support aliases, it use symlink.
	Solutions: 1. Do so that the pager support aliases (impossible:
	fvwm is feature freezed) 
	2. Added a symlink, but how and where ? (good solution)
	3. Present temporary solution: use the wait function or start only
	one pager !
	
	NOTE (not done !):
	In my opinion, other modules need to be configured in an other
	place:
	- Baker is a problem: may depends on desktopsize and pager config
	  Solutions: 1. putting desktopsize and baker in modules/ 
	  2. Fixing the numbers of desk (says 4) and use desk only Pager.
	  This is configurated in backer (not in modules/)
	  3. ???
	  Moreover,  we need to be able to disable backer, for a standard 
	  background or for a session or X background (see below).
	- Scroll, Identify, Form & script (default colors and font): 
	  in decoration !
	- Event (Audio): it can have its own config file: sounds and we
	  can enable it or disable it (in start ?)
	- Animate: in start, no problem for config.

	* bin/fvwm-themes-config:
	Do so that fvwm-theme-config do not look at file with a ".", "~"
 	and "#" in its name. # and ~ is for (x)emacs (may be we have to
	add other character). A point is for other editor (gvim) but in
	fact like that we can:
 	 - save a file: button --> buttons.orig
 	 - Or a sub main file can read files with a ".extension" in its 
	   directory (e.g., themes/redmond98/modules/main)
        and fvwm-themes will forget these files.

	* themes/{default,fvwm-icons,wm-icons}/iconstyle
	Since IconGrid and Icon/NoIcon is in modules I have renamed
	icons to iconstyle. This file gives the definition of the
 	icons and mini-icons to be used. Also, I have moved Iconfont
	into decorations (really natural).
	Added fvwm-icons for fvwm icons distribution (need more work,
	or better provide a simple and good set of icons with fvwm-themes,
	which is wm-icons compatible)
	Some works in wm-icons/iconstyle (MenuFvwmFvwmConfiguration is used
	in the place of WindowOps)
	
	* themes/default/background:
	* themes/redmond98/background:
	* themes/olicha/background:
	* themes/migo/background:
	Added backgrounds. Problem: we need to be able to disable background,
	for a backer or for a session or X background (see below).
        Use the "green" background for migo because I found a backgound that
	I prefer for the default (i.e., compatible with default/modules/main
	colors).
	
	* themes/default/style:
	Added:
	Style "FvwmConsole"     Slippery
	Is this a bad idea ?
	Note that the modules spec says that modules styles for "visible"
	modules may be defined in modules/ ; present style file break this
 	but this not a real problem, since modules/main is (and will be)
	read after this file. Added styles for FvwmScript
	
	* themes/default/functions:
	Added FuncFvwmDeiconifyFocusAndRaise
	Added FuncFvwmDeiconifyFocusAndWarp
	For modules
	
	* themes/default/desktop: Added GlobalOpts MouseFocusClickRaises 
	(dominik suggestion in the  fvwm-workers mailing list, it says that 
	the only reasonable focus policy is SloopyFocus or MouseFocus with the
	above option. I'm agree :o)
	Added the possibility of switching between page when moving a window.
	Edge Scroll is still disabled (a good thing for the default in my
	opinion)

	* themes/default/cursor: added "black white"

	* themes/default/binding:
	Mouse 1 on the border now move the window (for resize there are
	mouse 2 on the border or Mouse 1 on the window corner) This is fvwm
	default, ok it is not a good reason, but why we have "handles" ?

	* */desktop: Added some "restore default" destroyed by switching 
	between themes. Need more works: at least for migo (?) and afterstep
	(for afterstep I have copied the redmond98 one).
	Spec proposal for desktop:
	- Focus: SloppyFocus, ClickToFocus,  MouseFocus styles and global
	options: ClickToFocusDoesntPassClick / ClickToFocusPassesClick, 
	ClickToFocusDoesntRaise   /  ClickToFocusRaises,  
	MouseFocusClickDoesntRaise /  MouseFocusClickRaises
	- EdgeScroll, EdgeResistance,  EdgeThickness
	- Windows placement: smart/dumb, random/active, UsePPosition/NoPPostion
	GrabFocus/GrabFocusOff styles and SmartPlacementIsNormal/
	SmartPlacementIsReallySmart global opts.
	- Moving & Resize: ResizeOutline/ResizeOpaque style, OpaqueMoveSize,
	MoveSmoothness, HideGeometryWindow, SnapAttraction, Emulate
	- WindowShadeAnimate
	Note: all the above can be controlled by ScriptFvwmBaseConfig
	- Desktop size ???
	- ColormapFocus	FollowsMouse/FollowsFocus
	- Style * MWMFunctions, HintOverride, MWMDecor, OLDecor (is it
	reasonable to not use this ?)
	- Transient Windows styles
	- ClickTime and MoveThreshold 
	- XORValue or XORPixmap
	- SetAnimation
	- SaveUnder / SaveUnderOff style ??? (for slow server)
	- Some BugsOption: ModalityIsEvil, FlickeringMoveWorkaround(??)
	- BusyCursor ??
	Do I forget some thing ?
	I will do ScriptFvwmMiscBaseConfig when this spec will be fixed ...

	* */themes/xxx_disable_xxx: experimental theme for disabling some
	themes components (background, iconstyle)


	BIG PROBLEMS: It seems that fvwm-themes shows that there are
	some memory problems in fvwm (in particular in menus):
	a switch between themes (or reloading it) add more or less than 100K 
	of memory to fvwm ! After a numbers of switch the switching is
	slow ... for modules (pb with swallowing apps)
	It seems that we also need to unload the bindings and that
	we need to unload the non default styles ... 
	We need to be very careful with memory !
	Moreover, I've got a number of core dump ... 2.3.13 is alpha-beta
	at the present time ...

	TODO (IMHO): A lot of things. Some examples:
	- Be able to load individual component (already done I imagine)
	- Be able to unload some component.
	- Use FvwmTheme !
	- Put the stuff in cvs
	- Do not add to many themes !!
	For the future:
	- GUI interfaces
	- Split the installation site/users
	- Put all the images in a site directory
	- A perl script that build a user program menu.
	- During a user installation we need to ask questions to the
	user: e.g., what is your preferd term, editor, ... do you use
	kde/gnome menus ...etc. So that the components (e.g., buttons that
	start apps, Audio ..etc) can be builded so that the user like it
	immediatly. I think this point is important if you want that a
	lot of new linux users switch to fvwm.
 	- Add a lot of themes: maybe a fvwm-themes-contrib dist.
	
	BUGS: - redmond98/decorations config is uncompatible with the pager
	config of wm-icons/modules/main and default/modules/main and also
	with the IconTitle colors: the reason is that the real hilight color
	is given by a titlestyle command (so that the border of a window
	with the focus has the color of a normal window ... BorderStyle solid
	color doesn't work ...). Conversely, the pager of the FvwmBarButtons
	of redmond98 have the wrong color with the other decorations.
	Maybe FvwmTheme will allows to solve this.
	- If you use fvwm-icons/iconstyle with wm-icons/modules/main then
	we need to add wm-icons path to fvwm-icons path so wm-icons path
	is added two times if all its component are used.
	- I've not done the .xml files
	- a lot of other bugs ... hope that every things that can be destroyed
	is really destroyed (see the BIG PROBLEMS, here I forget bindings and
	apps styles).
	- Modules switching is not session award. Need to implement
	FuncFvwmSessionStart/QuitModulesTheme.
	
	CONCLUSION: I've done some works, but perhaps some of my ideas
	are not good. However, I think that the modules and desktop
	spec are really reasonable.
	
	Sorry for all the bad English !!
